parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, tachometer, and other gauges to malfunction or stop working, leading to a safety hazard as the driver is unable to monitor the vehicle's speed and performance.
symptoms: The speedometer and/or tachometer stick or jump erratically
the speedometer reads incorrectly or stays at 0 mph
the tachometer reads incorrectly or stays at a high RPM
the fuel gauge malfunctions
the oil pressure gauge pegs out
the water temperature gauge pegs out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and brake light system can cause the vehicle to be inoperable, leading to a safety hazard as the driver may not be able to stop the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The ABS light stays illuminated
the brake light stays illuminated
the vehicle fails state inspection due to ABS and brake light failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor operation can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to a safety hazard.
symptoms: The blower motor settings do not function properly
setting 5 does not work at all.
